{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a5f65d3e-95c4-4910-8f44-1a9b95969dca",
    "name": "Provenance Guard",
    "description": "AI201 Project 4 — showcase collection for the Provenance Guard Flask backend.\n\nRun order for a demo / portfolio walkthrough:\n1. **Submissions** — hits all three transparency-label variants (likely_human, uncertain, likely_ai), plus a validation-error example.\n2. **Appeals** — appeals the \"uncertain\" submission from step 1 (content_id is captured automatically), plus a 404 example for an unknown content_id.\n3. **Rate Limiting** — 12 requests in sequence against /submit; run this folder with Collection Runner (or click through fast) to see the first 10 return 200 and the last 2 return 429.\n4. **Audit Log** — GET /log, confirms every submission and appeal above landed in the structured audit trail.\n\nBefore running: start the app locally (`python app.py`, requires `GROQ_API_KEY` in `.env`) and confirm the `base_url` collection variable matches where it's listening (default `http://localhost:5000`).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:5000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "content_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1 — Submissions",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Submit - Likely Human",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has required fields\", function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('content_id');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('attribution');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('confidence');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('label');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"attribution is a valid category\", function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(['likely_ai', 'likely_human', 'uncertain']).to.include(json.attribution);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "console.log('attribution:', json.attribution, '| confidence:', json.confidence, '| label:', json.label);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"text\": \"ok so i finally tried that new ramen place downtown and honestly? underwhelming. the broth was fine but they put WAY too much sodium in it and i was thirsty for like three hours after. my friend got the spicy version and said it was better. probably won't go back unless someone drags me there\",\n  \"creator_id\": \"demo_human\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/submit",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["submit"]
            },
            "description": "Casual, irregular, first-person text — expected to land in the likely_human band (low combined score)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
